outputs.output_descr:
The GEF  mainstreaming Agro-biodiversity project is full size five years project (201-2015) has got three outcomes as follow:
Outcome 1: Enabling policy and institutional framework supporting in situ conservation of agrobiodiversity and crop wild relatives.
            Outcome 2: Crop Wild Relatives and farmer varieties are conserved in in situ gene banks      and on-farm conservation sites
              Outcome 3: Markets provide incentive for farmer uptake of agrobiodiversity friendly practices, particularly for wild Arabica coffee, enset, tef and durum wheat

project_descr: Mainstreaming Agr-biodiversity conservation into the Farming  System of Ethiopia
